main event: Two civilians observed an unidentified aerial object in Youngstown, Ohio on 10 March 1966.
interesting points: The object was reported to be round and white., The sighting lasted for 2 hours., Observers described the object as appearing to be lit from within., The object was evaluated as extremely bright, estimated to be 20 to 30 times the brightness of stars., The conclusion from the Air Force was that the object was likely Venus, based on its brightness and visibility.
witness description: Civilians with good reliability, observer from WKBN radio station
